theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_iff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔
      closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro h
    -- Using `h`, upgrade the basic inclusion `interior ⊆ closure`
    -- to obtain `univ ⊆ closure A`.
    have h_sub : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      simpa [h] using
        (interior_subset :
          interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X))
    -- The opposite inclusion is trivial.
    have h_sup : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := Set.Subset_univ _
    -- Conclude with equality of the two sets.
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm h_sup h_sub
  · intro h
    -- Rewrite `closure A` as `univ` and simplify.
    simpa [h, interior_univ]

theorem Set.Subset_univ {α : Type*} {s : Set α} : s ⊆ (Set.univ : Set α) := by
  intro x _
  simp

theorem Topology.closure_subset_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  simp
